        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3287562524" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1549135436872695879">This is somewhat similar to the superior <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4954833.Brooklyn' title='Brooklyn by Colm Tóibín' rel='nofollow noopener'>Brooklyn</a> in its examination of a seemingly affectless character; the point, of course, is that no one is really affectless. The structure was a little too obvious and clunky in this early work, but I was caught by the repressed neediness of Eamon by the end, as well as the beautiful descriptions of the coast and the sea. Rounded up to four stars. </span>
  <span id="freeText1549135436872695879" style="display:none">This is somewhat similar to the superior <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4954833.Brooklyn" title="Brooklyn by Colm Tóibín" rel="nofollow noopener">Brooklyn</a> in its examination of a seemingly affectless character; the point, of course, is that no one is really affectless. The structure was a little too obvious and clunky in this early work, but I was caught by the repressed neediness of Eamon by the end, as well as the beautiful descriptions of the coast and the sea. Rounded up to four stars. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1549135436872695879" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
