  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3286261728" />
    <a title="Celia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30261451-celia"><img alt="Celia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1466854747p2/30261451.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3286261728?book_show_action=true">Sep 21, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Celia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Celia" href="/user/show/30261451-celia">Celia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/19317021-the-heather-blazing">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=ten-year-challenge">ten-year-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=kindle-list">kindle-list</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=2020-read">2020-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=1001-challenge">1001-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30261451-celia?shelf=2020-rccc">2020-rccc</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3286261728" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3356476806530850576">Fantastic Historical Fiction.<br/><br/>&quot;At Boolavogue as the sun was selling O’er the bright May meadows of Shelmalier, A rebel hand set the heather blazing And brought the neighbours from far and near.”<br/><br/>This story takes place in Ireland.<br/><br/>A workaholic lawyer and his loving wife. He loves her very much too but seems unable to share his thoughts and himself with her (at least mentally).<br/><br/>The chapters switch between present time and growing up. All this in the first tense. We get to know Eamon better than his ow</span>
  <span id="freeText3356476806530850576" style="display:none">Fantastic Historical Fiction.<br /><br />"At Boolavogue as the sun was selling O’er the bright May meadows of Shelmalier, A rebel hand set the heather blazing And brought the neighbours from far and near.”<br /><br />This story takes place in Ireland.<br /><br />A workaholic lawyer and his loving wife. He loves her very much too but seems unable to share his thoughts and himself with her (at least mentally).<br /><br />The chapters switch between present time and growing up. All this in the first tense. We get to know Eamon better than his own wife.<br /><br />Politics plays a part too. Fianna Fail is the name of the party. Eamon de Valera is its candidate. Eamon Redmond, at the tender age of 17, writes and presents an oration on the great value of the party and its contender. It is through this association that Eamon meets Carmel, his future wife. She did not seem interested in him, but he persisted and they eventually married. <br /><br />I was impressed by the couple's relationship. Eamon was always extremely kind and considerate of Carmel, though it seemed hard to share himself with her.<br /><br />I have read 3 other books by Toibin, but I feel this the best. <br /><br />5.5 stars<br /><br />BTW, the author's afterward describes in detail his motivation for writing this book. I hope you take the time to read it too.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3356476806530850576" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


